# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# EUREKANOW — Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# HOW TO SET UP:
#   1. Copy this file to .env in the project root:
#        cp .env.example .env
#
#   2. Run supabase/schema.sql in your Supabase project:
#        Supabase Dashboard → SQL Editor → New Query → paste & Run
#
#   3. Get your keys from:
#        Supabase Dashboard → Settings → API
#        - "Project URL"       → REACT_APP_SUPABASE_URL
#        - "anon / public" key → REACT_APP_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#
#   4. (Optional) Set up Google Sign-In:
#        a) Go to Google Cloud Console → Create a project
#        b) Enable Google+ API
#        c) Create OAuth 2.0 credentials (Web application)
#        d) In Supabase → Authentication → Providers → Google:
#           - Enable Google provider
#           - Add your Google OAuth Client ID and Secret
#           - Add authorized redirect URI: https://anhsumvnxmxosdjclfss.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
#
#   5. Fill in the values below and restart the dev server (npm start)
#
# WITHOUT THESE KEYS the app runs in demo mode with local data.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

REACT_APP_SUPABASE_URL=https://anhsumvnxmxosdjclfss.supabase.co
REACT_APP_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_jRfD8wV05tWtSzCIoYFzHA_tBanaLw2